channel.title: Confusion opening up a .jar file
channel.description: so I go to run the Z-File search.. It just says "select a program from the list" or "Search the web" I just upated to java 7.0_52 and I think that this is what made it do this. I am just confused on what I should open the file up with.. help

item.title: Confusion opening up a .jar file
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

You shouldn’t have to open a .jar with anything aside from java.
So what you should do, is “select a program from the list” and it will have a “browse” option or button.
That should open directly to your program files. Navigate to your java, into the bin folder, and then java.exe
If you installed 32 bit java on a 64 bit computer, you’ll find it here: C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jre7\bin\java.exe
Otherwise it’s going to be here: C:\Program Files\Java\jre7\bin\java.exe
If you don’t have a jre7 folder in either, then go into the jdk folder. JDK all the same files in the “bin” folder, and probably more.
